House Resolution 241
By: Representatives Chastain of the 7th, Gambill of the 15th, and Efstration of the 104th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Edgar Land, the 2024 Citizen of the Year; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, through his lifelong commitment to service, mentorship, and leadership, Edgar
4 Land has made a profound and lasting impact on Gilmer County and beyond, resulting in his
5 recognition as the 2024 Citizen of the Year; and
6 WHEREAS, he is an active member of New Hope Baptist Church, where he serves as a
7 deacon and Sunday school teacher, mentors others through Bible studies, and shares his
8 musical talents as a pianist; and
9 WHEREAS, he extends his service beyond his church by leading Bible studies for residents
10 at The Oaks Assisted Living Facility, offering them spiritual guidance and fellowship; and
11 WHEREAS, Edgar Land has mentored countless young people throughout the community,
12 positively influencing their lives and guiding them toward success and fulfillment; and
13 WHEREAS, he has held leadership roles in numerous community organizations, including
14 the Ellijay Lions Club and the Rotary Club of Gilmer County, and has served as past
