15 president of the Coosawattee Shrine Club, Past Worshipful Master of the Oak Bowery
16 Lodge, and Past Grand Master of the Masons in Georgia, the highest office in Masonry; and
17 WHEREAS, as further testament to his dedicated service, he was awarded the Scottish Rite
18 Mason's 33rd Degree, a distinguished honor achieved by few; and
19 WHEREAS, he has additionally overseen impactful programs such as the Georgia Child
20 Identification Program (GACHIP), which provides comprehensive child recovery,
21 identification, and abduction awareness resources to parents; and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
23 appropriately honored during this special time.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body recognize and commend Edgar Land, the 2024 Citizen of the Year,
26 as well as extend sincere best wishes for future health, happiness, and success.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
28 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Edgar
29 Land.
